my life totally sucks.

1062
01:04:34,359 --> 01:04:36,192
But it'll all blow over.

1063
01:04:36,248 --> 01:04:37,405
Oprah or no Oprah,

1064
01:04:37,464 --> 01:04:40,225
they'll all forget that
stupid book ever existed.

1065
01:04:40,279 --> 01:04:41,884
Just look at Jonathan Franzen.

1066
01:04:41,944 --> 01:04:43,265
Who?

1067
01:04:43,320 --> 01:04:45,241
My point exactly.

1068
01:04:45,305 --> 01:04:47,586
Besides, all the cash my dad's
making from the book

1069
01:04:47,642 --> 01:04:49,659
is going into a trust fund.

1070
01:04:49,719 --> 01:04:52,284
When I turn 18,
I'm gonna be rich.

1071
01:04:52,345 --> 01:04:53,883
Me.

1072
01:04:53,944 --> 01:04:55,483
Not you.

1073
01:04:55,544 --> 01:04:57,497
Not we.

1074
01:04:57,560 --> 01:04:59,165
Me.

1075
01:04:59,224 --> 01:05:02,651
But I don't
want any of your money.

1076
01:05:02,713 --> 01:05:04,415
Yeah, right.

1077
01:05:04,473 --> 01:05:05,563
I don't.

1078
01:05:05,625 --> 01:05:07,611
When I turn 18,
I'll have my own money.

1079
01:05:07,673 --> 01:05:10,368
<i>- You wanna bet?
- On what?</i>

1080
01:05:10,425 --> 01:05:12,444
I'll bet you that you that my
dad's not our dad.

1081
01:05:12,505 --> 01:05:15,515
So I'm betting
that your dad is my dad?

1082
01:05:15,577 --> 01:05:16,668
You're a genius?

1083
01:05:16,729 --> 01:05:17,788
Really?

1084
01:05:17,849 --> 01:05:19,682
I never said
I was a genius.

1085
01:05:19,737 --> 01:05:22,715
And I never said
I'm a lesbo.

1086
01:05:22,777 --> 01:05:24,643
Bet.

1087
01:05:26,105 --> 01:05:28,539
I can't wait for you to meet my
Grandpa Stan.

1088
01:05:28,602 --> 01:05:31,329
You know, if it wasn't for him,
we would have never met.

1089
01:05:31,386 --> 01:05:32,608
I can wait to thank him.

1090
01:05:37,370 --> 01:05:39,169
Places like this depress me.

1091
01:05:39,225 --> 01:05:40,644
Why?

1092
01:05:40,697 --> 01:05:42,530
Is this it?

1093
01:05:42,585 --> 01:05:44,702
Is this where we end up?

1094
01:05:44,762 --> 01:05:49,792
Surrounded by old people who
reek of mothballs and menthol?

1095
01:05:49,850 --> 01:05:51,487
All of us just waiting to die?

1096
01:05:51,546 --> 01:05:52,987
Not my Grandpa Stan.

1097
01:05:53,051 --> 01:05:55,070
He reeks of
cigarettes and whiskey.

1098
01:05:55,131 --> 01:05:56,669
Cool.

1099
01:05:56,730 --> 01:05:58,563
Hey, everyone.

1100
01:05:58,619 --> 01:05:59,808
Where's Stan?

1101
01:06:02,683 --> 01:06:04,548
Nurse Bruna?

1102
01:06:04,601 --> 01:06:05,726
Where's my grandfather?

1103
01:06:11,323 --> 01:06:12,828
Stan?

1104
01:06:12,890 --> 01:06:15,422
Stan?

1105
01:06:15,483 --> 01:06:18,048
Stan!

1106
01:06:18,107 --> 01:06:19,297
Stan!

1107
01:06:22,587 --> 01:06:23,613
Henry, honey.

1108
01:06:26,012 --> 01:06:28,642
Patricia... where's Stan?

1109
01:06:30,362 --> 01:06:31,781
Come here, honey.

1110
01:06:34,523 --> 01:06:36,739
Please, Henry.

1111
01:06:36,796 --> 01:06:37,887
Please.

1112
01:06:42,492 --> 01:06:44,130
Where's Grandpa Stan?

1113
01:06:45,532 --> 01:06:48,064
I'm sorry, Henry, honey.

1114
01:06:48,124 --> 01:06:51,333
I'm so sorry.

1115
01:06:51,388 --> 01:06:53,189
Where is he, Mom?

1116
01:06:53,245 --> 01:06:54,435
Where is he?

1117
01:06:57,116 --> 01:06:58,370
Why aren't you in school?

1118
01:07:33,693 --> 01:07:35,232
( Thundering )

1119
01:07:57,086 --> 01:08:00,295
74 Nobel Laureates over
the course of this university's

1120
01:08:00,351 --> 01:08:02,086
illustrious history.

1121
01:08:02,143 --> 01:08:04,259
But never once has a tenured
faculty member

1122
01:08:04,318 --> 01:08:06,665
appeared on Oprah.

1123
01:08:06,719 --> 01:08:09,546
Oh, any publicity
is good publicity.

1124
01:08:09,599 --> 01:08:11,498
I'm sure things will go much
better next time

1125
01:08:11,552 --> 01:08:12,739
you're on Oprah.

1126
01:08:12,798 --> 01:08:15,112
Peddling your new book.

1127
01:08:15,166 --> 01:08:19,073
There isn't going to be
another book, Charles.

1128
01:08:19,135 --> 01:08:21,961
With all the funding
being poured into your work?

1129
01:08:22,015 --> 01:08:25,573
Henry... isn't my work.

1130
01:08:25,631 --> 01:08:27,170
No?

1131
01:08:27,232 --> 01:08:29,764
Then what is he?

1132
01:08:29,823 --> 01:08:31,242
<i>- He's--
- He's here</i>

1133
01:08:31,295 --> 01:08:33,129
because you
wanted him to be here.

1134
01:08:33,184 --> 01:08:36,971
He's here because we're paying
him a lot of money to be here.

1135
01:08:37,025 --> 01:08:38,693
He's here because of you.

1136
01:08:42,080 --> 01:08:45,354
You're right, Charles.

1137
01:08:45,408 --> 01:08:48,005
Henry is here...

1138
01:08:48,064 --> 01:08:49,056
because of me.

1139
01:08:51,808 --> 01:08:53,063
I understand that now.

1140
01:08:55,712 --> 01:08:56,869
Thank you, Charles.

1141
01:08:56,929 --> 01:08:58,217
Oh, please, Slavkin.

1142
01:08:58,272 --> 01:08:59,626
There's no need to
thank me.

1143
01:08:59,681 --> 01:09:01,187
My job is to manage.

1144
01:09:01,249 --> 01:09:03,167
Your job is to
publish.

1145
01:09:03,232 --> 01:09:04,552
Or perish.

1146
01:09:04,608 --> 01:09:06,660
Well, then you're just gonna
have to fire me, Charles.

1147
01:09:09,889 --> 01:09:11,078
Oh, wait a minute.

1148
01:09:11,138 --> 01:09:14,465
That's right,
you can't fire me.

1149
01:09:14,528 --> 01:09:16,002
I have tenure.

1150
01:09:52,515 --> 01:09:54,500
Am I going to
beat the odds?

1151
01:09:54,561 --> 01:09:56,940
Henry?

1152
01:09:56,994 --> 01:09:58,565
The transition from
prodigy to adult

1153
01:09:58,626 --> 01:10:00,743
is an extremely difficult one.

1154
01:10:00,803 --> 01:10:03,465
Only one in a 100 prodigies
succeed in becoming happy,

1155
01:10:03,522 --> 01:10:05,901
well-adjusted adults.

1156
01:10:10,820 --> 01:10:13,035
10,004 Post-it notes
of research.

1157
01:10:13,090 --> 01:10:16,747
Surely, you must have
arrived to some conclusion.

1158
01:10:16,804 --> 01:10:19,183
Am I gonna be that
one in a hundred?

1159
01:10:19,236 --> 01:10:23,523
You are a very...
special person.

1160
01:10:23,587 --> 01:10:25,126
I know what that means.

1161
01:10:25,187 --> 01:10:28,133
Someone of your...

1162
01:10:28,195 --> 01:10:32,550
extraordinary intellect
comes along...

1163
01:10:32,612 --> 01:10:35,623
maybe once in
a century, if at all.

1164
01:10:35,684 --> 01:10:37,483
I don't want to be
extraordinary.

1165
01:10:37,540 --> 01:10:40,651
But extraordinary
is exactly what you are.

1166
01:10:40,708 --> 01:10:42,695
I don't want to be the test
subject of your next book!

1167
01:10:42,757 --> 01:10:45,189
You're not, Henry,
you know?

1168
01:10:45,251 --> 01:10:47,532
I promise you,
despite what you see,

1169
01:10:47,588 --> 01:10:48,810
you're not.

1170
01:10:48,868 --> 01:10:50,309
All my eyes can see
is all I know.

1171
01:10:52,645 --> 01:10:54,696
I'm not writing
a book about you.

1172
01:10:56,676 --> 01:10:58,597
I thought I was,
but I'm not,

1173
01:10:58,661 --> 01:11:03,527
so you can
forget about all of this.

1174
01:11:03,588 --> 01:11:05,673
All of what you see.

1175
01:11:05,733 --> 01:11:07,119
I can't forget.

1176
01:11:15,877 --> 01:11:17,132
This arrived in the mail.

1177
01:11:17,189 --> 01:11:19,786
It's addressed to me,
but made out to you.

1178
01:11:19,845 --> 01:11:21,515
Thought you might be
interested in the results.

1179
01:11:32,454 --> 01:11:33,840
Where you going?

1180
01:11:35,751 --> 01:11:37,419
To help my mom
plan a funeral.

1181
01:12:47,753 --> 01:12:49,739
Ahh!

1182
01:12:54,183 --> 01:12:57,741
Ahh!

1183
01:14:05,131 --> 01:14:07,564
( Crying )

1184
01:14:33,901 --> 01:14:34,859
Billy?

1185
01:15:04,429 --> 01:15:06,578
Who is he?

1186
01:15:06,637 --> 01:15:07,958
I think he's my uncle.

1187
01:15:13,197 --> 01:15:14,670
Are you my Uncle Billy?

1188
01:15:18,093 --> 01:15:19,566
If you're my nephew.

1189
01:15:23,758 --> 01:15:25,712
This used to be my room.

1190
01:15:25,772 --> 01:15:28,272
<i>- Oh, yeah?
- Yeah.</i>

1191
01:15:28,333 --> 01:15:31,193
Four walls
and some left-over beads.

1192
01:15:32,398 --> 01:15:35,027
It's been 35 years.

1193
01:15:35,085 --> 01:15:36,504
Why didn't you come back

1194
01:15:36,558 --> 01:15:38,741
when President Carter granted
amnesty to the draft dodgers?

1195
01:15:38,798 --> 01:15:41,297
Back in '77?

1196
01:15:41,359 --> 01:15:42,581
Well, I guess I thought
I'd have time

1197
01:15:42,638 --> 01:15:46,031
to make amends.

1198
01:15:46,094 --> 01:15:47,218
<i>Guess that was wrong.</i>

1199
01:15:47,279 --> 01:15:48,632
You think?

1200
01:15:58,319 --> 01:16:00,718
Stan wanted you
to have this.

1201
01:16:00,782 --> 01:16:02,103
Is that a fact?

1202
01:16:03,343 --> 01:16:04,784
He told me so himself.

1203
01:16:06,223 --> 01:16:08,090
He wanted to pass it down to
one of his sons.

1204
01:16:20,975 --> 01:16:22,743
You're his grandson.

1205
01:16:23,920 --> 01:16:25,241
So you keep that.

1206
01:16:32,464 --> 01:16:35,377
The Vietnam War was one that
I, William Herman, opposed.

1207
01:16:35,440 --> 01:16:37,787
Due to my moral principles.

1208
01:16:37,840 --> 01:16:39,957
I do, however, sincerely
regret that in my absence

1209
01:16:40,017 --> 01:16:41,206
that I've missed a great
many things.

1210
01:16:41,265 --> 01:16:43,096
I have missed being a brother to
my brothers,

1211
01:16:43,151 --> 01:16:44,373
who have all since perished.

1212
01:16:44,432 --> 01:16:46,352
I have missed
being a friend

1213
01:16:46,416 --> 01:16:48,981
to the strongest person
I've ever known...

1214
01:16:49,040 --> 01:16:51,189
my sister.

1215
01:16:51,247 --> 01:16:54,292
I've missed
being Uncle Billy to...

1216
01:16:57,649 --> 01:16:59,831
He's a remarkable young man.

1217
01:16:59,889 --> 01:17:02,322
But I missed most of all...

1218
01:17:02,385 --> 01:17:03,673
being a son.

1219
01:17:07,729 --> 01:17:10,325
Of all my regrets,
my single greatest is knowing

1220
01:17:10,385 --> 01:17:13,463
that I'll never have the
opportunity to tell my father

1221
01:17:13,521 --> 01:17:14,875
how much I miss him.

1222
01:17:17,617 --> 01:17:19,156
How much I loved him.

1223
01:17:23,858 --> 01:17:26,290
I hate you, Billy Herman.

1224
01:17:26,354 --> 01:17:27,991
I hate you so much.

1225
01:17:42,226 --> 01:17:43,994
Mothballs and menthol.

1226
01:17:44,050 --> 01:17:46,812
You don't have to pretend like
you want to be here.

1227
01:17:46,866 --> 01:17:50,675
I could pretend to be polite,
courteous and communicative.

1228
01:17:50,738 --> 01:17:52,375
But I'm not.

1229
01:17:52,435 --> 01:17:53,624
I'm a teenager.

1230
01:17:53,683 --> 01:17:55,385
You're 12.

1231
01:17:55,443 --> 01:17:56,796
I'll be 13 in a week.

1232
01:17:56,851 --> 01:17:59,349
$0'?

1233
01:17:59,410 --> 01:18:01,462
So I could
pretend to be happy,

1234
01:18:01,522 --> 01:18:04,534
pretending that
you don't exist.

1235
01:18:04,595 --> 01:18:06,133
But I wouldn't be happy

1236
01:18:08,434 --> 01:18:10,748
After all,
you are my brother.

1237
01:18:15,412 --> 01:18:18,205
It's such a relief knowing
that Gunter's not our dad.

1238
01:18:18,260 --> 01:18:20,246
He was such a tool.

1239
01:18:20,308 --> 01:18:21,781
You saw
the lab report?

1240
01:18:23,188 --> 01:18:24,757
That means
you lost the bet.

1241
01:18:24,819 --> 01:18:25,976
That means I won.

1242
01:18:34,772 --> 01:18:37,118
Dad loved you
most of all.

1243
01:18:37,172 --> 01:18:38,678
Yeah, right.

1244
01:18:38,740 --> 01:18:40,279
I was an accident.

1245
01:18:40,341 --> 01:18:42,075
It was an accident
I was ever born.

1246
01:18:42,132 --> 01:18:44,762
Dad always wanted a girl.

1247
01:18:44,820 --> 01:18:46,774
After four boys in a row,
he finally got one.

1248
01:18:48,917 --> 01:18:50,236
You.

1249
01:18:56,309 --> 01:19:00,281
After he...

1250
01:19:00,341 --> 01:19:01,814
told Henry the truth,

1251
01:19:01,877 --> 01:19:03,416
I...

1252
01:19:05,558 --> 01:19:07,128
I wished he was dead.

1253
01:19:12,854 --> 01:19:14,621
Well, at least now you know.

1254
01:19:14,678 --> 01:19:15,931
That I wasn't an accident?

1255
01:19:15,988 --> 01:19:17,527
No, you'd better be
careful what you wish for.

1256
01:19:28,630 --> 01:19:29,951
Cool.

1257
01:19:48,662 --> 01:19:49,720
<i>Mom?</i>

1258
01:19:51,478 --> 01:19:52,832
<i>Mom?</i>

1259
01:19:52,886 --> 01:19:54,327
Yes, Henry, honey?

1260
01:19:54,391 --> 01:19:55,864
Who's this?

1261
01:20:03,191 --> 01:20:05,091
That's your Uncle Jimmy.

1262
01:20:05,143 --> 01:20:06,615
No, I mean that.

1263
01:20:08,790 --> 01:20:10,907
That's you, Henry, honey.

1264
01:20:13,495 --> 01:20:16,474
But I don't remember ever
meeting Uncle Jimmy.

1265
01:20:16,535 --> 01:20:18,587
How could you?

1266
01:20:18,647 --> 01:20:20,863
You were less than
a week old.

1267
01:20:20,920 --> 01:20:22,753
And you were sound asleep.

1268
01:20:25,463 --> 01:20:27,897
That was the day I told Jimmy
I named you after him.

1269
01:20:32,791 --> 01:20:35,137
Henry James Herman.

1270
01:20:37,592 --> 01:20:39,425
<i>I was named after
my Uncle Jimmy.</i>

1271
01:20:43,352 --> 01:20:46,179
A week later,
you were at his funeral.

1272
01:20:46,232 --> 01:20:47,618
Do you remember that?

1273
01:20:49,945 --> 01:20:51,036
Yeah.

1274
01:20:53,561 --> 01:20:54,947
Me too.

1275
01:20:59,512 --> 01:21:01,312
Why don't we put this...

1276
01:21:02,840 --> 01:21:04,281
back where it belongs.

1277
01:21:36,570 --> 01:21:38,208
Every book
should have a title.

1278
01:21:40,378 --> 01:21:42,757
Well, it could,
couldn't it?

1279
01:21:42,810 --> 01:21:44,447
I don't think so.

1280
01:21:44,507 --> 01:21:46,209
You said it yourself.

1281
01:21:46,267 --> 01:21:48,666
<i>My guess is
as good as yours.</i>

1282
01:21:48,729 --> 01:21:51,873
It's highly improbably that
the "H" stands for Henry.

1283
01:21:53,755 --> 01:21:57,825
Let's say that
you could go back in time.

1284
01:21:57,882 --> 01:22:00,163
Would you still publish
that book?

1285
01:22:00,219 --> 01:22:02,980
So many unintentional

1286
01:22:03,035 --> 01:22:04,868
great things

1287
01:22:04,924 --> 01:22:06,843
came to be
because of that book.

1288
01:22:06,906 --> 01:22:08,161
Just answer
the question, Dad.

1289
01:22:12,252 --> 01:22:13,758
Yes.

1290
01:22:13,820 --> 01:22:15,804
I most certainly...

1291
01:22:15,866 --> 01:22:18,180
would not.

1292
01:22:20,988 --> 01:22:22,558
No.

1293
01:22:22,618 --> 01:22:24,768
I would not publish
that book.

1294
01:22:29,532 --> 01:22:31,234
You can't change the past.

1295
01:22:31,292 --> 01:22:32,710
But you can
change the future.

1296
01:22:33,948 --> 01:22:35,137
Henry's right.

1297
01:22:36,476 --> 01:22:38,593
Today is my birthday.

1298
01:22:38,653 --> 01:22:40,670
And now that
I'm an adult...

1299
01:22:40,731 --> 01:22:42,685
I feel that a I have
a moral obligation

1300
01:22:42,748 --> 01:22:45,247
to help make
the world a better place.

1301
01:22:45,309 --> 01:22:46,400
You do?

1302
01:22:47,709 --> 01:22:48,548
You'?

1303
01:22:48,604 --> 01:22:50,917
You, me.

1304
01:22:50,972 --> 01:22:53,635
We should all be the change
we wish to see in this world.

1305
01:22:53,693 --> 01:22:55,112
Shouldn't we, Henry?

1306
01:22:55,166 --> 01:22:56,769
We should try.

1307
01:22:59,133 --> 01:23:01,828
That is why after much
thought and deliberation,

1308
01:23:01,885 --> 01:23:03,522
I, Audrey O'Hara,

1309
01:23:03,582 --> 01:23:05,697
on my 18th birthday,

1310
01:23:05,756 --> 01:23:09,762
will donate 20% of my trust fund
to the following organizations.

1311
01:23:12,573 --> 01:23:13,381
Okay, fine.

1312
01:23:13,438 --> 01:23:15,718
Make that 25%.

1313
01:23:15,773 --> 01:23:18,469
33 1/3%
and that's final.

1314
01:23:20,094 --> 01:23:21,699
I suggest you write
this down, Dad.

1315
01:23:21,758 --> 01:23:23,110
Uh...

1316
01:23:25,246 --> 01:23:26,206
Right.

1317
01:23:29,375 --> 01:23:31,108
Don't seem to have a pen.

1318
01:23:37,726 --> 01:23:39,231
Thank you, Henry.

1319
01:23:41,341 --> 01:23:42,727
Proceed.

1320
01:23:42,782 --> 01:23:44,223
The National Organization
for Women.

1321
01:23:46,751 --> 01:23:48,518
The Environmental Defense Fund.

1322
01:23:52,223 --> 01:23:54,755
The National Gay
and Lesbian Task Force.

1323
01:24:04,415 --> 01:24:07,142
My name is
Audrey Stravinowsky

1324
01:24:07,199 --> 01:24:08,585
and I am a lesbian.

1325
01:24:14,111 --> 01:24:16,938
